  "prompt": "If my ATM card is blocked for online transactions then how do i restart it?",
  "response": "If your ATM card is blocked for online transactions, you can generally restart or unblock it using the following steps:\n\n1. **Contact Customer Service:**\n   - Call your bank's customer support helpline. The number is usually provided on the back of your ATM card or on the bank's website.\n   - Explain the situation and request for your card to be unblocked for online transactions.\n\n2. **Visit Your Bank Branch:**\n   - Visit a nearby branch of your bank.\n   - Speak to a representative at the customer service desk or help counter and ask them to unblock your card.\n   - Bring valid identification and any other required documents.\n\n3. **Online Banking Portal:**\n   - Log into your bank's online banking portal or mobile app.\n   - Navigate to the section where you can manage your cards. This section may be labeled as \u2018Card Services\u2019 or something similar.\n   - Select the option to unblock or activate your ATM card for online transactions.\n\n4. **SMS/Email Service:**\n   - Some banks provide the option to unblock cards via SMS or email. Check your bank\u2019s website for details on whether this is available and the specific format to be used.\n\n5. **App Notification:**\n   - If your bank has a mobile app, it might allow you to unblock your card directly through the app.\n   - Check for any messages or alerts about the card status and follow the prompts to unblock it.\n\n6. **Security Check:**\n   - If there was suspicious activity leading to your card being blocked, you might need to verify your identity or provide additional information to prove it's really you attempting to unblock the card.\n\nKeep in mind the process and options can vary depending on your specific bank and locality. It's always best to refer to your bank\u2019s official resources or customer service for accurate guidance.",
